\section{Conclusion}

Generative Particle Theory (GPT) introduces a universal scalar field
$\mathcal{G}$ and its lowest-energy excitation $\psi$ as a minimal,
domain-agnostic mechanism for structure formation, stabilization, and repair.
The theory is formulated with a clear Lagrangian, well-defined particle mass,
symmetry structure, quantization, and propagator. Its core prediction is that
systems influenced by $\psi$ stabilize and organize faster than random or
known non-generative models allow.

The biological edition GPT-B specializes this framework to stem cells and
